<recipe>
<title>
Maple Cranberry Sauce
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 5 minutes
COOK TIME: 15 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 20 minutes
COURSE: Side Dish
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: cranberry, holiday
SERVINGS: 6 servings
</details>
<ingredients><ingredient amount="0.25 Cup">Orange</ingredient></ingredients>
<instructions>
Bring maple syrup, water, orange juice, and cranberries to a boil in a saucepan.
Reduce heat, and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, and stir in orange zest.
Pour cranberries into a serving dish, and let come to room temperature.
Cover, and chill until ready to serve.
</instructions>
<cuisine>American</cuisine></recipe>